    "body": "Can I help you and you help me? What are you having issues with running it? Install `grpio` (whichever version you like) and install `nose` and you should be set.\n\nYou'll need to replace `PROJECT_ID` and `ACCESS_TOKEN` with a valid project on the cloud console  (with the `datastore` API turned on) and with a valid token.\n\nYou can get a token quickly from the `gcloud` CLI by using `gcloud auth login` and then\n\n``` python\nimport oauth2client.client\n# Skip the GAE and GCE checks and just go for CLI.\ncreds = oauth2client.client.GoogleCredentials._implicit_credentials_from_files()\nprint(creds.get_access_token().access_token)\n```\n"
  },
