    "body": "> by how the problem requires execution by `nosetests`\n\nIt doesn't, I just ran it that way since I started out with the system test. I just re-ran without `nosetests`\n\n```\n$ LEAK=False python min_repro.py\n...\n$ LEAK=True python min_repro.py\n...\nE0829 13:20:23.015526485   20090 network_status_tracker.c:48] Memory leaked as all network endpoints were not shut down\n```\n\nI also tested your snippet with just `python` and it leaked.\n\n---\n\n> How severely are you affected?\n\nNot at all, in the sense that I don't have any applications in production that use gRPC. But it's a memory leak.\n\n---\n\n> How much of a problem would it be to wait for the fix in `grpcio` 1.1?\n\nYou tell me.\n"
